      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increasing the pick count will definitely tighten the weave, which will noticeably reduce the overall breathability of the cotton linen. While a denser weave can sometimes give a richer appearance, it will also make the fabric feel less airy and potentially stiffer. You should expect the hand-feel to become smoother but less soft, moving toward a more structured drape.",
