      "content": "Achieving a dense weave while maintaining a luxurious, soft hand-feel is a delicate balance, and the micronaire level is crucial here. If you push the density too high without compensating, the fabric will feel more stiff and less supple, losing that premium drape. To combat this, you might need to focus on the fiber quality itself—ensuring the Egyptian cotton is ultra-long and has low micronaire—and potentially incorporating a targeted finishing process to soften the dense structure post-weaving.",
